article.headline: Yale 66, Dartmouth 53
article.story: NEW HAVEN, Conn. (AP) -- Guard Edwin Draughan led four double-figure scorers for Yale with 13 points to lead the Bulldogs to a 66-53 win over Dartmouth Friday night. Forwards Caleb Holmes and Sam Kaplan and center Dominick Martin each had 11 points for the Bulldogs (6-12, 2-3). Dartmouth, which has lost each of its 11 road games, dropped to 5-15, 2-5. Center David Gardner led the Big Green with 11 points. There were 10 lead changes and seven ties, including 29-29 at halftime. Yale took the lead for good 38-36 on a Martin lay-up with 16:42 left. A 9-2 run gave the Bulldogs a 51-42 lead with 10:05 left. Yale held Dartmouth to 28.6 percent shooting in the second half and to just four field goals in the final 12:32. The Bulldogs shot 63.2 percent in the second half.
